Greece May Face a Debt Haircut of More Than 60 Percent, Juncker Tells ORF

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   T i r o n e
-- 
2011-10-11T05:26:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-11/greece-may-face-debt-haircut-over-60-percent-juncker-tells-orf.html
Luxembourg’s  Jean-Claude Juncker ,
who leads the group of euro-area finance ministers, said more
than 60 percent of  Greece ’s debt may need to be restructured.  While a Greek debt restructuring cannot be ruled out,
Juncker said late yesterday in an  interview  with  Austria ’s ORF
television, “all strenght must be used” to prevent a euro-area
country from going bankrupt.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
